        <h2>What else did you learn from WoZ that you will be implementing?</h2>
        <p>There are a few features that are "no-brainers" based on our WoZ testing.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The ability to see the camera feed before triggering the recording. This lets users set the shot and the frame before starting to record the video. Without this feature, many users inadvertently recorded stuff they didn't mean to record.</li>
            <li>The ability to see whether a user has seen your glimpse or not. Test users who provided glimpses said they wanted feedback from the other user about their glimpse. Has the other user seen it? What do they think of it? We're not sure yet what the best form of feedback is; for now, we're just sending read receipts.</li>
            <li>The ability to review your own glimpses, at will, after you've recorded and sent them.</li>
        </ul>    
