        <h2>What's your implementation status?</h2>
            <h3> iOS </h3>
            We have a functional iOS app. We can create accounts, request, send, and receive glimpses.All features mentioned above are implemented. Limitations are as follows:
            <ul>
                <li>No notion of "friends". Anyone can request a glimpse from anyone else on the system.</li>
                <li>Not leveraging the power of background processing and not reducing size of videos, so there can be significant lag when uploading / downloading videos.</li>
                <li>Not a slick or pretty user interface, but that's part of the point!</li>
            </ul>

            <h3> Android </h3>
            We were worried about our ability to distribute the iOS app to a large number of test users. There's a delay to getting apps approved on the app stores, and getting users outfitted for alpha testing on TestFlight is quite involved. Since this project is moving quickly, we decided putting all of our faith in iOS was too much of a risk. Android applications are significantly easier to distribute for testing, so we've begun developing for Android as well. Development has been slower and we are not yet fully functional. (We're missing the ability to record and send glimpses, which is pretty crucial...)
